@NODE "regulargame" "Regular Game Type"
@TOC "MAIN"

 REGULAR GAME TYPE

   This game type is like the one player mode. But now you are two
   snakes that have to battle for the numbers.
   Remember, the more numbers you pick up, the more points you get.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "surroundgame" "Surround Game Type"
@TOC "MAIN"

 SURROUND GAME TYPE

   In the surround game type the aim of the game is to trap the other
   player with your body. The fun part is that your tail just gets longer
   and longer all the time. And it never stops until one player is dead.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "options" "Game Options"
@TOC "MAIN"

 OPTIONS

   Here you setup the game as you like it.
   You change the settings by moving the cursor to the option that you
   wish to change and then press fire.

   LIVES: 1-5
      Number of lives each player has when he starts.

   SPEED: Slow, Medium or Fast
      This is how fast the snakes in the game moves.

   ADD: 3, 5 or 10
      This is how many bodyparts that are added to the end of the snake
      every time you pick up a number.

   Wrap: On/Off
      If wrapping is ON, then you can move through the grey walls at the
      top, bottom and sides of the screen.

   Music: On/Off
      This turns ON or switches OFF ingame music.

   Save Options
      This lets you keep the options that you have edited until the next
      time you start Snakes. If you only want to use the options you have
      edited in this Snakes session then you do not need to save.

   Back...
      This takes you back to the main menu.

@ENDNODE

