@NODE "leveledit" "Leveleditor Instructions"
@TOC "MAIN"

 LEVELEDITOR INSTRUCTIONS

   You control the cursor with a joystick in port 2.
   Depending on the current drawmode you can either draw or delete
   a block by pressing fire.

   Press SPACE to change the drawmode. (Draw/Delete)

   Press RETURN to change the current block to draw. (Rotates)

   Press 1 or 2 to place the starting position of either player.
      The cursor animation will stop until you have selected the
      starting direction by pressing a cursor key.

   Press DEL to clear the drawing area and start with the level.

   You can select which level to load or save by using the following keys:
      F1 = Level -1
      F2 = Level +1
      F3 = Level -10
      F4 = Level +10
      F5 = Level -100
      F6 = Level +100

   Press S to save the current level. But be careful so you don't
      overwrite an already saved level. Make sure that the position
      that you save to is empty.

   Press L to load the current level. This will erase the current edited
      level and display the loaded level instead.

   Finally ... Press ESC to quit to the Workbench.

   WARNING! Make sure that it is possible to get into and out of all
            empty spaces, or Snakes might put numbers where the players
            can't reach them.

@ENDNODE

